Three people were abducted on Monday August 31, by kidnappers who mounted a road block along Falgore Forest in Doguwa Local Government Area of Kano State. Daily Nigerian reported that an eyewitness, Ado Musa told Freedom Radio that the incident which happened around 7am left many commuters injured including the Hisbah commander of the local government, Mukhtar Abdulmumin. Kano Police Command spokesperson, Abdullahi Kiyawa confirmed the incident and also disclosed that the police have begun investigation into the incident. Source •Kano State Governor Abdullahi Ganduje A teenage boy (identity undisclosed) has been buried alive in an uncompleted building at Wase village, Minjibir Local Government Area of Kano State. Two persons, one Aminu Suleiman ‘m’ 29 years old and Abdulrashid Ishaq ‘m’ 32 years old all of Tudun Murtala Quarters Kano… December 31, 2019 In "Metro" The father of one of the children rescued in Anambra State has narrated how his son was kidnapped, According to PREMIUM TIMES. “When the police told me they were going to Onitsha in search of missing children, I never thought the investigation would yield any results concerning my son,” Muhammad… October 27, 2019 In "Security" Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Gunmen suspected to be kidnappers have abducted two Chinese working at a Glass and Aluminium company at Utese village, Ikpoba-Okha local government area. A police personnel attached to the Chinese workers was killed during the operation. Witnesses said the incident happened on Wednesday evening after close… July 4, 2019 In "News"